  "text": "Temporal abstraction of actions. Temporal abstraction of actions consists in using high-level actions, also called options, which can have different execution time [CITATION_1] . Each option is associated with an intra-option policy which defines the action (low-level actions or other options) to realize in each state when the option is executed. The length of an option, which is the number of executed actions when an option is chosen, is often fixed.",
